<P>
WILLIAM BENNETT RESIGNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Apparently Bennett, watching faithfully all these many months over our chemical 
morals, feels things are well enough in hand that he can turn the job over to 
someone else. Does this mean that he will start smoking again, or will he 
continue to get his nicotine by way of the special gum he started chewing when 
he took his anti-substance abuse show to Washington? 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT L. BRIGHAM, Manhattan Beach 
