<P>
November 19, 1990, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 21; Column 4; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
131 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NBA ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
DREXLER SCORES 30, PORTLAND IS PERFECT AT 9-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Clyde Drexler scored 30 points, the fourth consecutive game he has had at least 
that many, and the Portland Trail Blazers remained the NBA's only unbeaten team 
Sunday night with a 125-112 victory over the Bulls at Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
Portland (9-0) equaled a club record for its best start, set in 1979, when the 
Trail Blazers finished the season with a losing record. 
</P>
<P>
Drexler added nine assists and seven rebounds. Chicago's Michael Jordan had 20 
of his 29 points in the second half to go with seven assists and five rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Utah 103, Minnesota 94 -- Karl Malone scored 24 points and the Jazz ended a 
four-game losing streak by turning back the Timberwolves at Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
John Stockton added 22 points for Utah, and Tyrone Corbin and Tony Campbell 
each scored 24 for Minnesota. 
</P>
