<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHUMAN WINS FINAL SPRINT-CAR RACE AT ASCOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICH ROBERTS, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After all the speeches and all the tears, they finally ran the final sprint-car 
race at Ascot Park Saturday night, and Ron Shuman's victory seemed as 
inevitable as the closing of the little track. 
</P>
<P>
Shuman, the California Racing Assn. points leader from Tempe, Ariz., won the 
13th annual 50-lap Don Peabody Classic after passing leader Mike Kirby of Long 
Beach on the 42nd lap. 
</P>
<P>
Cary Faas of Yorba Linda finished second. 
</P>
<P>
About double the average attendance -- 8,224 -- was on hand and they stayed 
well after midnight. The feature race didn't begin until 11:37 p.m. and was 
slowed by two caution periods. 
</P>
<P>
The Peabody wasn't the track's last event. The curtain is scheduled to come 
down for good with Thursday night's running of the 50th 100-lap Turkey Night 
Grand Prix for USAC midget race cars. 
</P>
<P>
After 34 years, Ascot's lease expires Dec. 31. 
</P>
</TEXT>
