<P>
COLLEGE PROVIDES FOR AFFIRMATIVE ACTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former federal government employee who specialized in equal opportunities 
programs has been named Fullerton College's first affirmative action officer. 
</P>
<P>
George Beloz, 52, of Corona, will plan and implement the college's affirmative 
action program and policies. 
</P>
<P>
A native of Chicago, Beloz previously was a senior management analyst for the 
federal government's Defense Contracts Administration in Los Angeles. He has 
also worked as a grants contractor and education officer for the U.S. Agency 
for International Development and has been a high school and college teacher. 
</P>
<P>
Beloz received his bachelor's and master's degrees from Illinois State 
University, majoring in Spanish. He holds a doctorate in education from 
Southern Illinois University. 
</P>
