<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; 
</P>
<P>
OCC OFFERS $150,000 IN SCHOLARSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Scholarship applications for Orange Coast College's 1991-92 academic year are 
available in the dean of students office. 
</P>
<P>
Nearly $150,000 in scholarships will be awarded at the annual Honors Night 
banquet next May. 
</P>
<P>
Scholarship awards range from $200 to $2,000 each. 
</P>
<P>
Applications for general scholarships must be returned to the dean of students 
office by Feb. 11. The office is in the college Administration Building. 
</P>
<P>
The general category includes continuing and transferring scholarships. 
Students applying for continuing scholarships must complete 12 units by the end 
of the 1990 fall semester and be enrolled in a minimum of six units next 
spring. Spring classes begin Jan. 22. 
</P>
<P>
Students who receive scholarships are required to have a 3.3 cumulative grade 
point average. 
</P>
<P>
Students applying for transferring scholarships must complete 42 units by the 
end of the fall semester and have a grade point average of 3.5. They must 
complete 56 units by the end of the 1990-91 academic year. 
</P>
<P>
The Scholarship Committee, which includes faculty, staff and students, 
considers a student's financial need, grade point average, service and 
leadership, employment and exceptional personal and academic circumstances, 
when awarding the scholarships. 
</P>
<P>
Applications for specialized technology, music, visual arts and consumer and 
allied health scholarships are due Feb. 22. Those scholarships are judged 
according to individual skill and departmental criteria. 
</P>
<P>
The dean of students office is open from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. Monday through 
Friday. For scholarship information, call (714) 432-5730. 
</P>
