<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
AUSTRALIA CHANNEL 7 PLANS CUTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SYDNEY, Australia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The troubled Channel Seven television network announced today it would cut 100 
jobs and freeze executive salaries for two years. 
</P>
<P>
The job eliminations hit four of the network's five stations in Sydney, 
Melbourne, Perth and Brisbane, chief executive Bob Campbell said. 
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Channel Seven said economic conditions had become considerably 
worse in recent weeks and forced the network to act to ensure its economic 
viability. 
</P>
