<P>
AUTO WORKERS OK CHRYSLER PACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DETROIT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United Auto Workers said today that its members have ratified the last of 
its three-year contracts with the Big Three auto makers, overwhelmingly 
approving an agreement with Chrysler Corp. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement, covering about 63,000 active hourly and salaried workers, was 
ratified in voting last week by a margin of better than 4 to 1, UAW spokesman 
Bob Barbee said. 
</P>
<P>
Precise figures were unavailable. 
</P>
<P>
The union initially focused its bargaining efforts on General Motors Corp., and 
bargainers reached tentative agreement Sept. 17. Less than a week later, a 
tentative agreement was reached with Ford Motor Co. The UAW and Chrysler 
reached tentative agreement Oct. 30. 
</P>
<P>
Each contract provides for a 3% base wage increase in the first year, 3% 
lump-sum payments in the second and third years and increases for current and 
future retirees. 
</P>
