<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
WARNER WANTS TO CALL THE SHOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Malcolm-Jamal Warner believes that he's ready for life after "The Cosby 
Show" -- behind the camera. 
</P>
<P>
"I've been preparing to be a director since I was 17," Warner says in an 
interview published in the Nov. 24 issue of TV Guide. 
</P>
<P>
"I knew I had to learn it." 
</P>
<P>
Warner, 20, has starred as Bill Cosby's son, Theo, on the hit series for seven 
years. 
</P>
<P>
"Where do I go from here? To think that I reached my peak as a teen-ager would 
be a sad and scary thought." 
</P>
<P>
He directed his first episode of "The Cosby Show" last spring and is set to 
direct two more episodes this season. He's negotiating to direct a feature 
film, has already directed six music videos and is co-producing four television 
children's specials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
